The SwiftUI‑native way to capture a view as a bitmap is to use the **ImageRenderer** type (available starting with iOS 16 / macOS 13). You create an ImageRenderer with the view you want to capture, optionally set the desired size and scale, and then ask the renderer for its rendered image (UIImage on iOS, NSImage on macOS). This produces a bitmap that can be saved, shared, or otherwise processed.

