Use the `sheet(item:onDismiss:content:)` modifier, binding it to an optional `@State` variable. When the optional is non‑nil, the closure receives the unwrapped item and you can present the detail view. Example:

```swift
@State private var selectedItem: Item?

var body: some View {
    List(items) { item in
        Button(item.name) { selectedItem = item }
    }
    .sheet(item: $selectedItem) { item in
        DetailView(item)
    }
}
```
This is the cleanest, idiomatic way to present a detail sheet from an optional in SwiftUI.

